{"id": "duc04-testb-24:6#18", "contents": "When Alfred Nobel wrote the directions establishing a literature prize in his name, he chose an unclear word and scratched out a few letters, leaving questions about the prize that have engaged and piqued the literary world ever since. A new chapter in the mystery will be written Thursday, when the Swedish Academy announces this year's winner of the world's most prestigious prize for writers. The prize focuses intense media attention on the Swedish capital and raises the question: Why does the world care so much about the literary choices of a handful of people in a quiet and remote country?"}
